Track separately:
 - openbsd port (for upstream)
 - rust patchs (unrelated to openbsd port, but for upstream)
 - packaging stuff (which will stay local)
 - ...

The directories tracks patchs from:
 - 01-openbsd : https://github.com/semarie/rust/tree/openbsd/
 - 02-ports: local patches

Git export:
$ git format-patch -N snap-XXX..openbsd-XXX

Regen patches with:
$ make clean extract
$ cat ./tracked-patches/*/* | patch --batch -V t -d $(make show=WRKSRC) -p1
$ find $(make show=WRKSRC) -name '*.~1~' -execdir $PWD/tracked-patches/rename-patch.sh {} \;
$ make update-patches

